Usage: uniquify [-help] [-exclude <module>+] [-verbose] { <design|module> | -new_master <hinst>+ }

-help                    # Prints out the command usage
<topCell|vCell>          # Uniquify inside the <design> or <module> and
                         # recursively below it, so all hinsts inside have
                         # their own unique module (except for -exclude
                         # modules). Multiple hinst references to <module>
                         # itself will remain as clones if that is already
                         # true. ((topCell|vCell), required)
-exclude <module>+       # These modules will be excluded from unification.
                         # This is useful if you know a specific sub-module is
                         # a partition that will only be implemented once and
                         # will be shared. ((vCell)+, optional)
-new_master <hinst>+     # Split out the hinst clones of one master module into
                         # clones of a new master. The new master is also
                         # uniquified (except -exclude modules). It is possible
                         # an hinst above will be forced to have a new master
                         # also (see Examples below). It is an error if any
                         # hinst is not a clone of the same module.
                         # ((hInst)+, required)
-verbose                 # Report any hinst clones that are uniquified.
                         # (bool, optional)